<p> In Chinese traditional medicine, it is believed that malfunctioning of the liver can be established by to the state of the patient's eyes.
<p> The liver and eyes are connected by energy channels. If bad energy rises from the liver to the eye area, then an effect such as dry eyes occurs, and the person does not see clearly. Later vision begins to deteriorate, myopia arises.
<p> Some time after the start of the exercise, the practitioner may feel discomfort in the eye area - “sand in the eyes”, pain. This is due to the fact that bad qi rising to the eyes is not completely thrown out but is partially delayed in them.
<p> After a month of practice for most practitioners the state of the liver improves significantly.